<form>
  <label>Contextual Drilldown</label>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <table>
        <title>Incidents By Category</title>
        <searchString>index=sfpd | top Category</searchString>
        <earliestTime>0</earliestTime>
        <latestTime>now</latestTime>
        <option name="height">200px</option>
        <drilldown>
          <set token="showChart1">true</set>
          <unset token="showChart2" />
          <set token="s_category">$row.Category$</set>
        </drilldown>
        <option name="wrap">true</option>
        <option name="rowNumbers">false</option>
        <option name="dataOverlayMode">none</option>
        <option name="drilldown">cell</option>
        <option name="count">10</option>
      </table>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <chart depends="$showChart1$">
        <title>Top Districts for Incidents related to: "$s_category$"</title>
        <searchString>index=sfpd Category="$s_category$" | top PdDistrict</searchString>
        <earliestTime>0</earliestTime>
        <latestTime>now</latestTime>
        <option name="charting.axisLabelsX.majorLabelStyle.overflowMode">ellipsisNone</option>
        <option name="charting.axisLabelsX.majorLabelStyle.rotation">0</option>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleX.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleY.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleY2.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.axisX.scale">linear</option>
        <option name="charting.axisY.scale">linear</option>
        <option name="charting.axisY2.enabled">false</option>
        <option name="charting.axisY2.scale">inherit</option>
        <option name="charting.chart">bar</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.nullValueMode">gaps</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.sliceCollapsingThreshold">0.01</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.stackMode">default</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.style">shiny</option>
        <option name="charting.drilldown">all</option>
        <option name="charting.layout.splitSeries">0</option>
        <option name="charting.legend.labelStyle.overflowMode">ellipsisMiddle</option>
        <option name="charting.legend.placement">none</option>
        <option name="height">300px</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.rangeValues">[]</option>
        <option name="charting.legend.masterLegend">null</option>
        <option name="charting.seriesColors">[0x293E6A, 0x77BA9B, 0x3B5998, 0x639BF1, 0xB6A754, 0xC9E1C1, 0xFF9900, 0xFF5A09, 0x0F9FB4, 0x1D2F3E]</option>
        <drilldown>
          <set token="showChart2">true</set>
          <set token="s_district">$row.PdDistrict$</set>
        </drilldown>
      </chart>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <map depends="$showChart2$">
        <title>Map of "$s_category$" in the "$s_district$" District</title>
        <searchString>index=sfpd Category="$s_category$" PdDistrict="$s_district$" | geostats latfield=Y longfield=X binspanlat=0.2 binspanlong=0.2 count</searchString>
        <earliestTime>0</earliestTime>
        <latestTime>now</latestTime>
        <option name="mapping.data.maxClusters">200</option>
        <option name="mapping.drilldown">all</option>
        <option name="mapping.map.center">(37.76,-122.43)</option>
        <option name="mapping.map.zoom">12</option>
        <option name="mapping.markerLayer.markerMaxSize">100</option>
        <option name="mapping.markerLayer.markerMinSize">4</option>
        <option name="mapping.markerLayer.markerOpacity">0.6</option>
        <option name="mapping.tileLayer.maxZoom">20</option>
        <option name="mapping.tileLayer.minZoom">0</option>
        <option name="mapping.data.bounds">(14.944784875088372,-172.96875,44.84029065139799,-46.40625)</option>
        <option name="mapping.tileLayer.url">http://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png</option>
        <option name="drilldown">all</option>
        <option name="mapping.seriesColors">[0x293E6A]</option>
        <option name="height">350px</option>
      </map>
      <chart depends="$showChart2$">
        <searchString>index=sfpd Category="$s_category$" PdDistrict="$s_district$" | timechart count</searchString>
        <earliestTime>0</earliestTime>
        <latestTime>now</latestTime>
        <option name="charting.legend.masterLegend">null</option>
        <option name="charting.seriesColors">[0x293E6A, 0x77BA9B, 0x3B5998, 0x639BF1, 0xB6A754, 0xC9E1C1, 0xFF9900, 0xFF5A09, 0x0F9FB4, 0x1D2F3E]</option>
        <option name="height">150px</option>
        <option name="charting.axisLabelsX.majorLabelStyle.overflowMode">ellipsisNone</option>
        <option name="charting.axisLabelsX.majorLabelStyle.rotation">0</option>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleX.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleY.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleY2.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.axisX.scale">linear</option>
        <option name="charting.axisY.scale">linear</option>
        <option name="charting.axisY2.enabled">false</option>
        <option name="charting.axisY2.scale">inherit</option>
        <option name="charting.chart">column</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.nullValueMode">gaps</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.rangeValues">[]</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.sliceCollapsingThreshold">0.01</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.stackMode">default</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.style">shiny</option>
        <option name="charting.drilldown">all</option>
        <option name="charting.layout.splitSeries">0</option>
        <option name="charting.legend.labelStyle.overflowMode">ellipsisMiddle</option>
        <option name="charting.legend.placement">none</option>
      </chart>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <html>
        <h2>Contextual Drilldown</h2>
        <p>Build interactive dashboards that enable users to drill-in to charts and tables on the page.  The behavior is supported through several key features:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Ability to use click events to set and unset token values.  Rather than redirect users to another dashboard, use the drilldown configuration to set tokens for consumption within the page</li>
          <li>Ability to show or hide dashboard elements based on the existance of a token value</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To enable contextual drilldown, do the following:</p>
        <h3>Step #1: Configure drilldown to set/unset tokens rather than link to another page</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Use set and unset to pass variables to other elements on the page.  For example:</li>
               <ul>
                 <li>To set a token to control show/hide, you may use something like: <code><![CDATA[<set token="showTable">true</set>]]></code></li>
                 <li>To pass click information, <code><![CDATA[<set token="s_sourcetype">$$row.sourcetype$$</set>]]></code></li>
                 <li>To pass click information and format it, <code><![CDATA[<set token="s_sourcetype">sourcetype="$$row.sourcetype$$"</set>]]></code></li>
               </ul>
            <li>Either configure the same action to be taken for all field/column clicks, or use conditions to enable distinct behaviors</li>
          </ul>
            <p>To enable the same action across all fields/columns:</p>
            <pre><![CDATA[
<drilldown>
    <set token="showTable">true</set>
    <set token="selected_sourcetype">$row.sourcetype$</set>
</drilldown>]]></pre>
        <p>To enable conditional actions for each field/column:</p>
            <pre><![CDATA[
<drilldown>
  <condition field="sourcetype">
      <!-- for the column sourcetype, do the following -->
    <set token="showTable">true</set>
    <set token="selected_sourcetype">$click.value2$</set>
    <unset token="showChart"/>
  </condition>
  <condition field="*">
      <!-- for all other columns, do the following -->
    <set token="showChart">true</set>
    <set token="count">$row.count$</set>
    <unset token="showTable"/>  
  </condition>
</drilldown>]]></pre>
        <h3>Step #2: Use token to control show/hide of dashboard elements</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>To only show a dashboard element based on the existence of a token, use: <code><![CDATA[<chart depends="$showChart$">]]></code></li>
          <li>To hide a dashboard element based on the existence of a token, use: <code><![CDATA[<chart rejects="$showTable$">]]></code></li>
          <li>To only show an element based on tokens in existence, and other tokens not in existence, use: <code><![CDATA[<chart depends="$token1$, $token2$" rejects="$token3$">]]></code></li>
        </ul>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>
</form>
